    "type": "experiment",
    "title": "Lightning2Earthcare experiment",
    "description": "Lightning2EarthCARE is a workflow for collocating EarthCARE satellite observations with lightning detections from geostationary sensors. It queries EarthCARE MSI and CPR data, retrieves lightning observations from MTG-LI and GOES-GLM, and performs spatial–temporal matching between the datasets. The pipeline clusters lightning detections, generates collocated datasets, and produces a catalogue of lightning storms sampled along the EarthCARE nadir track.. This experiment links the workflow and product.",
